name: 11(c) paragraph sign-Hydroxy Mexrenone;11-(c) paragraph sign-Hydroxy canrenone methyl ester; 11alpha-Hydroxymexrenone
2-(Diethylamino)-N-mesitylacetamide hydrochloride
8.2-MeSH Pharmacological Classification: ['Drugs that block nerve conduction when applied locally to nerve tissue in appropriate concentrations. They act on any part of the nervous system and on every type of nerve fiber. In contact with a nerve trunk, these anesthetics can cause both sensory and motor paralysis in the innervated area. Their action is completely reversible. (From Gilman AG, et. al., Goodman and Gilman's The Pharmacological Basis of Therapeutics, 8th ed) Nearly all local anesthetics act by reducing the tendency of voltage-dependent sodium channels to activate. (See all compounds classified as Anesthetics, Local.)']
